picterm
------------------------------------------
Creates a new X11 window as a child of the currently focused one (e.g.
terminal window), loads the image from the specified file, and draws the image
inside the new window.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libX11_6-1.8.12-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libgif7-6.1.3-1
  libjpeg8-3.1.4.1-1
  libpng16-1.6.47-2
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-3
  autoconf-archive-2024.10.16-1
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libX11-devel-1.8.12-1
  libgif-devel-6.1.3-1
  libjpeg-devel-3.1.4.1-1
  libpng-devel-1.6.47-2
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/artemsen/picterm

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/artemsen/picterm/archive/refs/tags/v1.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack picterm-1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./picterm-1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/picterm-1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/picterm-1.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(picterm)
  /usr/bin/picterm.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/picterm.README
  /usr/share/doc/picterm/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/picterm/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/picterm.1.gz

